reply.author: Nil val
reply.text: @Toy Fwd I work in the oil and gas Industry. I don't have anything against oil and gas industry. In fact I think the environment activists are totally wrong and barking at the wrong tree. Having said that, I know one thing for sure. Solar energy is changing India. I used to see power poles with street lights which do not function at all. They were connected to a power source with kilometers of copper/ aluminium cable. Now I see the with a tiny solar panel and an LED bulb which actually work all night and turns off automatically in the morning. Heavy vehicles will use fossil fuels. But look around you. How many heavy vehicles do you see for every car or bike on a street. Military vehicles will use fossil fuels. How many vehicles do a country own in comparison to the vehicles owned by citizens in the same country. I will come back to heavy vehicles. I have seen quite a few prototypes for big trucks ( aka lorries) that will run on electric. Yes, these will be short distance commuters. However, if you know anything about trucking/ transportation industry, you will the percentage of short distance commuters are much higher percentage than long distance ones. Trains and ships move the bulk. And wait for Hyper loop one.. If that become a reality... Would be interesting to watch the goods movement. Also watch how many entrepreneurship ventures are coming up with bikes and 3 wheelers in India. May take a few years but I foresee Indian crude consumption falling by more than half.
